==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Garth
<hw>Garth</hw> <pr>(g⟦aum⟧rth)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>gar⟦edh⟧r</ets> yard. See <er>Yard</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
close; a yard; a croft; a garden; <as>as, a cloister
<ex>garth</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A clapper clapping in a <qex>garth</qex>⟦br⟧
To scare the fowl from fruit.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dam or weir for catching fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Garth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Garth
<hw>Garth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<er>Girth</er>.]</ety> <def>A hoop
or band.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Garuda</ent>⟦br⟧
